Forecasts of hurricane activity are issued before each hurricane season by noted hurricane experts like Dr. [[William M. Gray]], and his associates at [[Colorado State University]]. A normal season, as defined by NOAA, has 6 to 14 named storms, with 4 to 8 of those reaching hurricane strength, and 1 to 3 major hurricanes. The [[June 2]], [[1987]] report suggested that eight tropical storms would form during the 1987 season, five of them becoming hurricanes.<ref name="Seasonalforecasters">
{{cite web
| author=The Advocate
| year=[[1987-06-02]]
| title=Hurricane Death Toll May Be Much Higher
| publisher=The Advocate
| accessdate=2007-10-12
| url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=AD&p_theme=ad&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0EB47467926FE137&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM
}}</ref> However, the forecasts proved too high, as only seven tropical storms formed, three of them hurricanes.<ref name="MWR"/> 

The 1987 Atlantic hurricane season had 14 tropical depressions form from [[May 25]] to [[November 5]]. Seven of the depressions strengthened into tropical storms, six of them named.<ref name="MWR"/> (Tropical Depression Two was upgraded into a tropical storm in post-season analysis, and has no name.) Tropical Storms Arlene, Emily and Floyd all reached hurricane status during their period.<ref name="Seasonalactivity-3">
{{cite web
| author=The Frederick Post
| year=[[1988-06-02]]
| title=Hurricane Death Toll May Be Much Higher
| publisher=The Frederick Post 
| accessdate=2007-10-11
| url=http://www.thehurricanearchive.com/Viewer.aspx?img=10277635_clean&firstvisit=true&src=search&currentResult=9&currentPage=0
}}</ref> Only one of the three, Emily, reached major hurricane status. Tropical Depression Fourteen may have been a tropical storm in its lifetime, but it remains a tropical depression. 

The United States only got affected by four tropical systems this year, Tropical Depression One, which hit [[Florida]], the unnamed storm which hit the [[Gulf Coast]], while Hurricane Floyd and Tropical Depression Fourteen struck [[Florida]] as well.<ref name="Seasonalactivity-1">
{{cite web
| author=The Advocate
| year=[[1987-12-01]]
| title=Hurricane season ends; U.S. gets break in '87
| publisher=The Advocate
| accessdate=2007-10-11
| url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=AD&p_theme=ad&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0EB474A441208832&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM
}}</ref><ref name="Seasonalactivity-2">
