==Storms==
===Tropical Depression One===
{{storm path needed}}
{{infobox hurricane small
| name=Tropical Depression One
| category=depression
| type=tropical depression
| image=TD 1L 26 may 1987 2006Z.jpg
| formed=[[May 25]]
| dissipated=[[June 1]]
| highest winds=35&nbsp;[[miles per hour|mph]] (55&nbsp;[[kilometres per hour|km/h]])
| lowest pressure=1000&nbsp;[[mbar]] ([[hPa]])
| hurricane season=1987 Atlantic hurricane season
}}
A low-pressure area was researched by a Reconnaissance Aircraft and declared it the first tropical depression of the year on Monday, [[May 25]], one week before the official season began.<ref name="TD1-2">
{{cite web
| author=Miami Herald
| year=[[1987-06-01]]
| title=1ST TROPICAL DEPRESSION OF YEAR FORMS IN ATLANTIC
| publisher=The Miami Herald
| accessdate=2007-03-17
| url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=DM&p_theme=dm&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0ED3CF3A24F4850A&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM
}}</ref> The depression was {{convert|350|nmi|km|-1}} from the east central Bahamas, whilst moving at about {{convert|8|mi/h|km/h|0|abbr=on}}. The depression moved towards [[Florida]] and stalled off the coast, producing thundershowers across the state on [[May 28]].<ref name="TD1-3">
{{cite web
| author=Steven K. Doig
| year=[[1987-05-31]]
| title=TROPICAL DEPRESSION TO DAMPEN WEEKEND
| publisher=The Miami Herald
| accessdate=2007-03-17
